The paper discusses the use of anonymization systems to secure a public database, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the development, deployment, and maintenance of decentralized systems, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DS). The use of a public database also falls under the category of databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the wider value of anonymization systems within the internet infrastructure, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the cost of developing and maintaining decentralized systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
